# PORT-NOTE (#1448): per-role model policy for the interactive 4-role chain, distributed via the three-role-model
#   plugin so every consuming repo inherits Option A (Opus on planner + both review gates, Sonnet on the executor).
#   Generated byte-identical from ai-brain canonical config/cc-roles.env by scripts/sync-three-role-plugin.mjs;
#   never hand-edit. In the plugin the ledger helper lives at bin/3role-ledger.mjs (the comment below names it
#   hooks/3role-ledger.mjs in ai-brain-canonical form — comment-only, nothing reads the config's comments).
# Per-role model+effort policy for the INTERACTIVE 4-role chain (#1448).
# Extended with a per-tier MODEL-VERSION pin table (#1458) — see the enforcement matrix below.
#
# Namespaced CC_ROLE_* to avoid collision with cc-models.env (the Ollama cron/benchmark pipeline's bare
# PLANNER_MODEL / EXECUTOR_MODEL, which name Qwen tags — a DIFFERENT model universe; keep the files separate).
#
#   model   in {opus, sonnet, haiku, fable}      (the Agent/Task `model:` tier)
#   effort  in {low, medium, high, xhigh}        (reasoning effort)
#   version = a concrete claude-* model id       (the tier's blessed EXACT edition — see the pin table below)
#
# ── PER-LEVER ENFORCEMENT MATRIX (#1458 — honest split: every lever states what is a hard wall vs a note) ───
#   | Lever         | Enforced how                                                    | Surface                     |
#   |---------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------|
#   | MODEL TIER    | MECHANICALLY — transcript message.model -> modelIdToTier ->     | completion gate (hard block)|
#   |               | compare to CC_ROLE_<ROLE>_MODEL. Fail-safe to opus.              | + leading-edge advisory     |
#   | MODEL VERSION | MECHANICALLY — transcript message.model == the pinned claude-*  | completion gate ONLY (the   |
#   |               | id (assert-latest / fail-on-drift). Fail-CLOSED on can't-tell   | spawn tool sees a tier      |
#   |               | ONLY when a pin is configured; DORMANT (no check at all) when   | ALIAS, never a concrete     |
#   |               | no pin is set for that tier/role.                                | version, at spawn time)     |
#   | EFFORT        | REAL per-role (#1466): a dedicated agents/cc-<role>.md agent-    | agent-def effort:            |
#   |               | definition's effort: frontmatter overrides the inherited SESSION | frontmatter (the mechanism) |
#   |               | effort -- the override lives in the DEFINITION, not a spawn-tool  | + ledger effort field       |
#   |               | param (there still isn't one). OBSERVABLE: the ledger effort      | (assigned at SPAWN,          |
#   |               | field is sourced from the SubagentStop hook's effort.level (the   | observed at CLOSE via       |
#   |               | harness's OWN signal -- NOT the transcript, which never carries    | SubagentStop effort.level   |
#   |               | it); the OBSERVED value overwrites the ASSIGNED one on conflict.  | -- observed wins)           |
#   |               | No BLOCKING gate enforces it yet (a completion-time hard gate is  |                              |
#   |               | a clean follow-up, out of scope here) -- real + observed, not yet  |                              |
#   |               | mechanically enforced. CONSUMER NOTE: this config ships the       |                              |
#   |               | POLICY + the observability channel to every plugin consumer;      |                              |
#   |               | REALIZING the mechanism needs the consumer's OWN agents/cc-<role>  |                              |
#   |               | .md definitions (ai-brain-local this ticket, not ported here).    |                              |
#
# FAIL-SAFE (MODEL TIER): a missing/malformed file OR a missing/invalid per-role *_MODEL key => that role
# falls back to OPUS (today's all-Opus behavior). NEVER fail-open-to-cheap — a typo must cost quality-safe
# Opus, not silently a weaker tier. `node hooks/3role-ledger.mjs resolve-role-model --role <role>` reads this
# file (fail-safe to opus) and is the single command the orchestrator + both model hooks consume.
#
# OPTION A (cost-aware mix, operator-chosen 2026-07-03): Opus on the seats where a mistake is expensive
# (orchestrator + planner + BOTH review gates); Sonnet on the highest-volume grunt seats (executor + the
# NEW research seat). This stretches the monthly usage bar without weakening any quality gate. See the plans
# `.ai-workspace/plans/2026-07-03-1448-per-role-model-policy.md` and
# `.ai-workspace/plans/2026-07-03-1458-per-role-control-surface.md`.

# Orchestrator = the always-on MAIN session (not a spawned subagent). Policy/lint entry only — NOT
# transcript-enforced (there is no per-orchestrator subagent transcript to read). NEVER pin to fable (the
# config lint refuses it: a 2x-Opus always-on seat burns the Fable bar). Effort bumped high -> xhigh (#1458,
# operator decision 2026-07-03: the orchestrator now "thinks harder").
CC_ROLE_ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL=opus
CC_ROLE_ORCHESTRATOR_EFFORT=xhigh

# Planner — a mistake here mis-shapes the whole run; keep the strongest tier + highest effort.
CC_ROLE_PLANNER_MODEL=opus
CC_ROLE_PLANNER_EFFORT=xhigh

# Plan-review — the first quality gate; Opus.
CC_ROLE_PLAN_REVIEW_MODEL=opus
CC_ROLE_PLAN_REVIEW_EFFORT=high

# Executor — the highest-volume seat (types the most); Sonnet is plenty-capable and much cheaper. This is the
# one seat Option A moves DOWN from Opus. Effort high -> medium (#1466, operator decision 2026-07-04): now that
# effort is REAL per-role (a dedicated agent-definition, not just a policy row), the executor is the seat where
# the cost-down mix makes most sense -- medium suffices for briefed mechanical work on the highest-volume seat.
# Operator-tunable: one config line; bump back to high if NEEDS-WORK loops rise.
#   Cost-down alt (opt-in, NOT a default): CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_MODEL=haiku for trivial-mechanical work only —
#   raises NEEDS-WORK loops on anything non-trivial, so set it per-run, never standing.
CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_MODEL=sonnet
CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_EFFORT=medium

# Execution-review — the LAST line of defense before ship; Opus (a Sonnet reviewer may miss subtle bugs).
CC_ROLE_EXECUTION_REVIEW_MODEL=opus
CC_ROLE_EXECUTION_REVIEW_EFFORT=high

# Research/search seat (NEW, #1458) — the ad-hoc Explore/research subagents the orchestrator spawns for
# lookups. Sonnet is plenty-capable for a search/summarize seat at a fraction of Opus cost. NOT one of the
# four transcript-enforced REQUIRED_ROLES (planner/plan-review/executor/execution-review) — this seat is
# resolvable via `resolve-role-model --role research` (the orchestrator passes model:sonnet at spawn time) but
# is never gate-blocked at completion time (it is not a REQUIRED_ROLE). Effort high -> medium (#1466): a
# search/summarize seat doesn't need high effort either. DEFERRED (out of scope for #1458): wiring this seat
# into either gate — file a follow-up only if research spawns start being tagged 3ROLE_TASK:... ROLE:research.
CC_ROLE_RESEARCH_MODEL=sonnet
CC_ROLE_RESEARCH_EFFORT=medium

# Cost-up alt (opt-in, NOT a default seat): CC_ROLE_PLANNER_MODEL=fable for the HARDEST one-off plans only.
# Fable is ~2x Opus and its subsidised usage bar expires ~July 7-8 — after that a Fable-pinned seat bills
# out-of-pocket. The config lint emits a cost-cliff warning on any *_MODEL=fable. Never auto-selected.

# ── MODEL-VERSION pins (#1458 — assert-latest / fail-on-drift) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# A tier alias ("sonnet") resolves to the tier's LATEST concrete version, revealed only in the transcript
# message.model. Pin the exact latest we last blessed; the completion gate FAILS LOUDLY if a role's
# transcript model != the pin (the platform silently bumped the latest, OR a role ran on an unexpected
# version) so a human updates the pin DELIBERATELY. Update path = edit here, then re-run the plugin sync.
# A tier with NO pin here leaves the version sub-leg DORMANT for every role at that tier (the tier leg alone
# still enforces) — deliberate, not a gap: it lets a consumer adopt tier enforcement (#1448) without opting
# into version drift-detection (#1458) until it is ready to bless a first pin.
CC_TIER_OPUS_VERSION=claude-opus-4-8
CC_TIER_SONNET_VERSION=claude-sonnet-5
CC_TIER_HAIKU_VERSION=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
CC_TIER_FABLE_VERSION=claude-fable-5
# Optional per-ROLE override (default UNSET): assert one role must run an exact version, overriding the
# per-tier pin for that role's expected tier. Rarely needed (the spawn alias can't select an OLD version) —
# this is an ASSERTION knob (validate one seat mid-migration), never a SELECTION knob.
#   CC_ROLE_EXECUTOR_MODEL_VERSION=claude-sonnet-5
